2026-07-24T05:57:25.2464044Z               "id": "d911c9d8009286df2e37da9a499264445a6b570c",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2475628Z               "message": "Add external IdP auth: OIDC SSO for users and JWT bearer for service accounts\n\nTwo new optional auth methods run alongside the existing token auth, each\nindependently enable/disable-able (token-only, SSO-only, or both):\n\n- Auth:Oidc — interactive single sign-on via any OIDC-compliant IdP\n  (Entra ID conventions by default). Adds a \"single sign-on\" button to the\n  login page; sessions use a signed ednsv-session cookie (Data Protection\n  keys persisted under DataDir/keys), so the UI and Swagger \"Try it out\"\n  work exactly like token sessions. Admin/standard role is mapped from a\n  configurable role claim (default: Ednsv.Admin app role).\n- Auth:JwtBearer — IdP-issued OAuth2 access tokens (e.g. Entra client\n  credentials) accepted on Authorization: *** service accounts,\n  with audience validation and the same role mapping (username app:{azp}).\n\nThe hand-rolled gate middleware stays the single enforcement point; external\nprincipals are normalized into the existing AuthService.User shape via a new\nExternalUserMapper (claim-driven, never persisted; usernames colliding with\nthe root user are rejected). SSO admins can issue tokens when token auth is\non — issuance-tree visibility works unchanged.\n\nThe fail-closed startup guard now keys off \"no auth method enabled\" instead\nof just the token hash, and RequireAdmin / /api/auth/me / /api/debug/proxy\nuse an explicit auth-bypass marker so token-auth-disabled-but-SSO-on\ninstances never treat every caller as admin.\n\nNew endpoints: GET /api/auth/methods (public), GET /api/auth/oidc/login,\nGET /api/auth/oidc/logout (single logout, opt-in). POST /api/auth/logout\nalso clears the SSO session.\n\nAdds a WebApplicationFactory integration test project (token regression,\nJWT bearer with test-signed tokens, auth-mode matrix, OIDC challenge) plus\nExternalUserMapper unit tests, and documents everything in\ndocs/configuration.md and a new docs/entra-setup.md walkthrough.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PRd7GEH8at5RYwqsD6AdGN",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2483673Z               "timestamp": "2026-07-22T03:49:16Z",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2484020Z               "tree_id": "91ab1466a5b722093075a19071294cd21664ec0f",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2484557Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/d911c9d8009286df2e37da9a499264445a6b570c"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2485064Z             },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2485291Z             {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2485504Z               "author": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2485790Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2486116Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2486403Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2486686Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2486898Z               "committer": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2487166Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2487463Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2487717Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2487963Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2488178Z               "distinct": false,
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2488484Z               "id": "4e7e81cc55b163b8ac51b84cf39980b2f777d7bf",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2495432Z               "message": "Add config revision history and elevated revoke for external admins\n\n- External-IdP admins (SSO / JWT) can now revoke any token, since they sit\n  outside the token issuance tree. AuthService.Revoke gains an `elevated`\n  flag that bypasses the ancestor check; the revoke endpoint sets it for\n  admins authenticated via oidc/jwt. The config root user `ednsv` remains\n  unrevocable, and token admins keep their issuance-subtree scoping.\n\n- Every config save is now backed up. ConfigService persists a capped\n  (~300) revision history to {DataDir}/config-history.json, each entry\n  recording the saved config, the user who saved it, and the timestamp. A\n  baseline \"(initial)\" revision is seeded on first load so the first change\n  is recoverable. Replace(incoming, savedBy) records the change; the PUT\n  /api/config endpoint passes the caller's username.\n\n- New admin-only endpoints GET /api/config/history (metadata, newest first)\n  and GET /api/config/history/{id} (the saved config). The Config page shows\n  a revision dropdown (\"date — user\"); selecting one loads it into the form\n  and JSON views for review before saving as a new revision.\n\nAdds unit tests (elevated revoke, revision recording/persistence/cap) and\nintegration tests (history endpoints, user attribution incl. SSO, and the\nSSO-admin revoke matrix), and documents both features in configuration.md.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PRd7GEH8at5RYwqsD6AdGN",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2501282Z               "timestamp": "2026-07-22T11:03:54Z",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2501643Z               "tree_id": "42c08e1fb47c2f9c5e65e0b23278c98fea568891",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2502189Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/4e7e81cc55b163b8ac51b84cf39980b2f777d7bf"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2502660Z             },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2502860Z             {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2503045Z               "author": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2503469Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2503778Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2504039Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2504292Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2504505Z               "committer": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2504776Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2505066Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2505324Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2505571Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2505764Z               "distinct": false,
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2506096Z               "id": "c85aa5e1fcf8efe3af8f0c7bdb0388ed1ccad334",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2512420Z               "message": "Add audit logging for security-sensitive ops and validation, with masking\n\n- Security-sensitive operations now emit audit log entries under a dedicated\n  Ednsv.Audit category: token/SSO sign-in (success + failure/rejection),\n  token issue/revoke/delete, config changes, the proxy diagnostic, and cache\n  flush — each recording the actor and key details.\n- Domain validation requests log user, domain, and input flags (smtp/http/\n  dnsbl/directDns/doh, recheck, DKIM count) for both the async job and the\n  sync endpoint; job completion logs performance — duration, check count,\n  severity breakdown, and DNS cache hits/misses.\n- When trace masking is enabled (MaskTrace=true, the default) usernames and\n  domains in all of the above — and in the per-request log scope — are masked\n  with the existing deterministic TraceMasker hash, so entries stay\n  correlatable without exposing identities. A null-safe Disp() helper centralizes\n  this; the request/job/sync scopes now mask the username (previously it was\n  logged in the clear).\n\nAdds a capture-logger test harness and integration tests asserting audit\nentries are emitted and that domain/username are masked by default but raw\nwhen MaskTrace=false. Documents the audit event catalog and masking behavior\nin configuration.md.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PRd7GEH8at5RYwqsD6AdGN",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2517768Z               "timestamp": "2026-07-22T11:25:33Z",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2518087Z               "tree_id": "5cc232996dc51527202a99459f840106216e9df0",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2518788Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/c85aa5e1fcf8efe3af8f0c7bdb0388ed1ccad334"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2519766Z             },
