2026-07-24T05:57:25.2522037Z               "committer": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2522284Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2522562Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2522791Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2523016Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2523207Z               "distinct": false,
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2523492Z               "id": "8fa19c84ef1d3b3405ded7d35cbeea74518d5f7f",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2527339Z               "message": "UI: never truncate SPF/DKIM/DMARC/TXT details; only truncate when it hides >=5\n\nThe results view capped each check's informational detail lines at 20 with a\n\"...and N more\" line. Two problems:\n\n- Critical email-DNS records (SPF mechanisms, DKIM selectors, DMARC tags, raw\n  TXT records) could be hidden behind the cap — exactly the records operators\n  come to read in full. These categories are now never truncated.\n- The cap fired even when it hid just 1-4 lines, producing a pointless\n  \"...and 1 more\" that saves no space. It now only truncates when >=5 lines\n  would be hidden (so the smallest possible \"...and N more\" is \"...and 5 more\");\n  21-24 detail lines render in full.\n\nErrors and warnings on any check were already shown in full and are unchanged.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PRd7GEH8at5RYwqsD6AdGN",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2531002Z               "timestamp": "2026-07-22T23:07:48Z",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2531346Z               "tree_id": "47a0a6a80eed3c1e7cb7e213c6ca95659f969d7d",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2531855Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/8fa19c84ef1d3b3405ded7d35cbeea74518d5f7f"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2532288Z             },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2532470Z             {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2532655Z               "author": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2532898Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2533177Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2533412Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2533646Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2533841Z               "committer": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2534093Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2534364Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2534596Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2534823Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2535013Z               "distinct": false,
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2535288Z               "id": "58009fa3c9bbae95f579bb737f2a501e212e1178",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2539806Z               "message": "Add \"recheck all\" option to force a full cache bypass\n\nRecheck was only offered scoped to prior issues (Warnings+/Errors+/Critical),\nand the post-result recheck buttons only appeared when there were issues. Add\nan explicit \"recheck all\" that bypasses every cache type and re-runs all checks\nagainst fresh data, regardless of prior results.\n\n- API: recheckSeverity=\"all\" (POST /api/validate) and ?recheck=all (sync GET)\n  set RecheckDeps = CacheDep.All directly, independent of the domain summary.\n  StartValidation gains a recheckAll flag; the validation-requested audit log\n  reports recheck=all.\n- UI: \"Recheck all (ignore cache)\" added to the top recheck dropdown, and an\n  \"All\" button that is always shown after a result (the severity-scoped buttons\n  still appear only when there are issues to target). Status label reads\n  \"(recheck all)\".\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PRd7GEH8at5RYwqsD6AdGN",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2546112Z               "timestamp": "2026-07-22T23:22:55Z",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2546664Z               "tree_id": "66c3c75ec5f4e73bc38377d29da19e8e5037756d",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2547510Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/58009fa3c9bbae95f579bb737f2a501e212e1178"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2548256Z             },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2548554Z             {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2548857Z               "author": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2549260Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2549898Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2550297Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2550684Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2551008Z               "committer": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2551413Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2551873Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2552264Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2552653Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2552976Z               "distinct": false,
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2553620Z               "id": "a296a4a3e45a1cbba082e7714b86d11682f63815",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2561683Z               "message": "Add admin-only cache-clear (memory + disk) endpoint and UI control\n\nAdds POST /api/cache/clear (admin-only) that wipes every cache: the in-memory\nDNS/SMTP/HTTP probe caches, the in-memory recheck summaries, and all on-disk\ncache files. Distinct from the existing /api/cache/flush, which only persists\nmemory to disk.\n\n- Core: Clear() on ProbeCache/ProbeCacheValue (MemoryCache + export log +\n  in-flight map); ClearCache() on DnsResolverService (query/PTR/server/AXFR\n  caches + unreachable-server state), SmtpProbeService, HttpProbeService;\n  DiskCacheService.Clear() deletes the known cache files (and leftover .tmp)\n  while leaving unrelated files; CacheManager.ClearAllAsync() clears memory\n  before disk so a concurrent flush can only re-persist an empty cache.\n- UI: a \"Maintenance\" panel on the admin-only config page with a prominent\n  warning that clearing degrades performance until caches re-warm, plus a\n  confirm() dialog before the call.\n- The action is audited at Warning level (Ednsv.Audit) with the actor.\n\nTests: DiskCacheService.Clear deletes cache files but preserves others and\nno-ops on a missing dir; the endpoint returns 200 for admins, is audited, and\n403s for standard tokens.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PRd7GEH8at5RYwqsD6AdGN",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2570210Z               "timestamp": "2026-07-22T23:30:22Z",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2570757Z               "tree_id": "be2e52c713e7963eeccc50f62594873aa00fa42e",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2571600Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/a296a4a3e45a1cbba082e7714b86d11682f63815"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2572375Z             },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2572661Z             {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2572952Z               "author": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2573340Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2573804Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2574190Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2574573Z               },
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2574883Z               "committer": {
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2575280Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-07-24T05:57:25.2575708Z                 "name": "Claude",
